Description: FedNow Service Scope

The account activity totals report is the message the FedNow Service uses to provide a FedNow participant with a summary of value and nonvalue messages that were processed by the FedNow Service for a given funds-transfer business day and associated with the given FedNow participant.

FedNow Service Usage

The account activity totals report is used by FedNow participants for reconciliation purposes.

The FedNow Service will send the report to all FedNow participants, on an unsolicited basis, after the close of the FedNow funds-transfer business day.

A FedNow participant can solicit the report during a FedNow funds-transfer business day to obtain a summary at a certain point in time, or for up to 90 previous FedNow funds-transfer business days by sending an account report request (camt.060) message to the FedNow Service. If the FedNow participant requests and account activity totals report for a range of FedNow Service funds-transfer business days, then the FedNow Service will send a separate account activity totals report for each individual FedNow Service funds-transfer business day within the range of days.
Generated by the MyStandards web platform [https://www.swift.com/mystandards] on 2023-06-01T13:54:05+00:00
